A 'Libellula fulva' is a type of dragonfly belonging to the family Libellulidae. 
The dragonfly has an average wingspan of around 8.5 cm. 
It has a bright orange-brown body with black markings. 
The wings are transparent with a reddish-brown tint and black spots. 
This species of dragonfly can generally be found near slow-moving bodies of water, such as ponds and streams. 
During adulthood, 'Libellula fulva' feeds on smaller insects, including flies and mosquitoes. 
The 'Libellula fulva' belongs to the order Odonata, which is characterized by its ability to fly in all directions, hovering ability, and large eyes.
